cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.LO. 

The paper focuses on understanding generalization in reinforcement learning, which is a core problem in machine learning. The use of the reparametrization trick and the study of reparameterizable RL using supervised learning and transfer learning theory suggest a focus on the theoretical aspects of RL. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the relationship between the generalization gap and the environment transition, reward, and agent policy function class, which suggests a focus on system-level aspects of RL, leading to the inclusion of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.LO (Optimization and Control) as possible sub-categories.
